description:
Step into the comfort of this stylish studio situated in the very heart of Belltown. It promises a relaxing retreat within walking distance to the vibrant Downtown, world-famous Space Needle, top restaurants, shops, entertainment, and attractions.

Adventure through the city and then retreat to the lovely studio whose cozy design will satisfy your every need.

✔ Comfortable Queen Bed

Learn more below!

It offers everything you would ever need for a perfect carefree stay in an attractive studio space with a contemporary design that complements the fantastic location in the very heart of the booming Belltown. The nightlife is indeed booming, so keep that in mind while booking.
 
It conveniently combines the living room, fully equipped kitchen, and dining area with the bedroom to create a modern setting for the ideal stay. Large windows allow the natural light to accent the cozy carpeted floors during the day, while luxury lighting enriches the lavish ambiance in the evening, enhancing the feeling of elegance.

Modern interior design featuring carefully picked amenities and decorations make this lovely studio. You can quickly change your setting by moving a few steps around this well-furnished apartment.

The apartment has a fully equipped kitchen that makes it suitable for preparing any meal that comes to your mind. A well-stocked kitchen in a studio space is a rare occurrence, perfect for those who would like to prepare delicious, homemade meals.

Look no further than our comfortable studio for your visit to Seattle, WA. We are looking forward to you experiencing it in its complete comfort and coziness.

The studio is exclusively yours, without interruption during your stay, so relax, unwind, and make yourself at home.  

Other than the already mentioned amenities, our home also offers: 

✔ Wi-Fi 

✔ Air Conditioning (portable unit)

✔ Heating

We will be accessible 24/7 for our guests via phone, text, or the booking app. Expect a quick and prompt response. We give our guests space but are available for every inquiry. Please know that we do have business hours and are "off-duty" from 9pm to 9am for nonemergency issues, but will get back to you as close to 9am as possible.

Contact us now so we can begin arranging your perfect vacation!

The studio is nestled in Belltown, the waterfront neighborhood adjacent to downtown Seattle. It offers a hip, youthful area with lots to do. It's ranked as one of the most walkable neighborhoods in Seattle, making getting to all its boutiques, art galleries, restaurants, nightclubs, and bars an easy exercise. 

Belltown is bordered on the north by Lower Queen Anne, east and south by Downtown Seattle, and on the west by Elliot Bay.

***Distance times are calculated if traveling by car.

If you arrive by car, you will be happy to know that we offer one free parking spot in the garage.  However, it is in an underground garage, next to a concrete wall, so the smaller the vehicle the better. There is also additional paid parking in a lot beside the building. If you would like to avoid driving during your stay, there are many convenient, easily accessible transportation options close to our home.

itemListElement.name: Festive Flavors of Pike Place Market Holiday Food Tour

name: Festive Flavors of Pike Place Market Holiday Food Tour
description:
Embark on a culinary journey through Pike Place Market's festive traditions!

This guided tour invites you to explore, taste, and celebrate the holiday spirit at Pike Place Market. Experience the seasonal flavors and traditions with delicious savory and sweet tastings from 9 unique businesses.

As you indulge in seasonal delights from the market's beloved favorites, you'll also discover new spots that are becoming local gems. Along the way, hear the fascinating stories behind the entrepreneurs who started these iconic shops.

review.name: Great thing to do with visitors in town for the holidays
review.reviewBody: Judson was famtastic and knew so much about the market which really added to the experience. Our group was comprised of all ages, ranging from 10-86 and all loved this tour with a holiday twist. We went back to places we discovered on the tour the next day. I am a Seattle resident and love to bring visitors on Savor tours.

review.name: Loved it!!!
review.reviewBody: Judson was amazing… so knowledgeable about the market and very passionate about what he was sharing. So special to learn from someone who knows the market so well and getting to meet some of the producers was a plus. I’m a local native and I STILL learned a lot! Highly recommend this tour!!!

review.name: Great tour for visitors or locals
review.reviewBody: We had an amazing time on our tour with Judson! We are locals and have been to Pike Place Market many times. Every stop was at a place we hadn't been to, or included food we hadn't tried before. We also learned some new things about the history of the market. We loved so much of the tour that we went back to shop at several tour stops before heading home. Highly recommend!

review.name: Holiday Tour Fun
review.reviewBody: I went with seven friends, coworkers in hospitality industry. We had such a good time. Judson was really fun and so knowledgeable.  We were almost all native Seattle’s but learned so much about what the market does and what being a vendor entails. Lots of history of businesses which solidifies them in your shopping possibilities. The samples were excellent. I will highly recommend this your tour to friends and family. Judson is the best.  He made the entire experience in the pouring rain wonderful.

itemListElement.name: Private Ballard Locks, Gasworks Park and HouseboatsTour!

name: Private Ballard Locks, Gasworks Park and HouseboatsTour!
description:
Let's explore the busiest locks in the nation, the Hiram Chittenden Locks! We will watch boats "lock through" and watch for baby salmon (smolts) going out to sea, and adults returning to navigate the fish ladder on their way home to spawn. The resident harbor seals and herons are always fun to watch too! We will learn how this critical component of our maritime industry and history transformed Seattle, and it's role in managing our fresh water lake systems. Then we're off to Gas Works to learn about this one-of-a-kind park, where we will see float planes taking off and landing, and enjoy stunning views of the city. Finally we will visit to the houseboat communities along Lake Union, a uniquely Seattle experience!

Kids aged 8 and up are welcome, as I do not have car seats for younger ones.

review.name: Great Tour!  Unique stops only a local would know, very educational and fun!
review.reviewBody: Highly recommend letting Lynn show you the city!!  Lynn is a great guide with energy and a wealth of knowledge about the city.  If you are looking to truly experience Seattle and see things a little more like the locals do, you will love this!  The private tour gave us the ability to flex our route and make additional stops based on our interests.  She even offered her number in case we had any issues or needed any assistance for the remainder of our stay.  Weather you are there for a long weekend or moving to the area - she is a great resource for learning about the city.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Ballard Locks, Gas Works Park and Houseboats Tour

name: Seattle Ballard Locks, Gas Works Park and Houseboats Tour
description: Let's explore the busiest locks in the nation, the Hiram Chittenden Locks! On this walking and driving tour, we will watch boats "lock through" and learn how the locks operate. In the late spring, we can visit the largest Great Blue Heron colony in the city to watch and listen to the chicks, and see baby salmon (smolts) going out to sea. From mid-June through September we will see adult salmon returning to navigate the fish ladder on their way home to spawn. We will learn how this critical component of our maritime industry and history transformed Seattle, and its role in managing our freshwater lake systems. Then we're off to Gas Works to learn about this one-of-a-kind park, where we will see float planes taking off and landing, and enjoy stunning views of the city. Finally we will visit the houseboat communities along Lake Union, a uniquely Seattle experience! For a private version of this tour (1 to 4 people) please call/text

review.name: Amazing tour
review.reviewBody: Tour was amazing! Saw a lot that goes “under the radar.” Extremely knowledgeable guide and super friendly. Got to see a lot of places that most may not.

review.name: A wonderful overview of the major components that comprise Seattle.
review.reviewBody: Lynn, our tour guide, was VERY knowledgeable.  She recognized our particular personalities and we shared as we explored.  She delivered much more than advertised while including neighborhood tours with accompanying local information.  Her narration was easy to hear even in the large vehicle that Lynn uses.  A very comfortable and easy vehicle for us to get both in and out.  Overall, the most memorable and enjoyable event on this visit to Seattle.

review.name: Ballard, Freemont and more
review.reviewBody: Lynn was super. It turned out to be a private tour and she tailored everything to our interests. Great transport, walking tons as well. Lynn is very knowledgeable, personable and easy to hang with. Even in the rain.

review.name: I’m glad I went!
review.reviewBody: The tour guide is a long-time resident of the area, very knowledgeable, and obviously passionate about the people, culture, history, and environment of Seattle. You’ll see some great views, beautiful neighborhoods, hidden gems, as well as get recommendations for whatever else you’re interested in doing, seeing, or eating while you’re visiting.

review.name: Excellent small group tour in Seattle!!!
review.reviewBody: Lynn was AMAZING! This was the best small group tour we have ever booked. Lynn was extremely friendly, accomdating & knowledgeable. She also recommend 2 excellent restaurants. We ended up eating at & enjoying both restaurants during our vacation. I highly recommend this tour!

review.name: You MUST do this tour!!!!!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I had done most “common” Seattle sights!  The tour company owner and tour director had so many “off the radar” things to show us.  We saw things we didn’t even know existed.  Everything was enjoyable and we especially enjoyed Lynn’s knowledge of the area and her recommendations for things to do on the remainder of our trip.  When we return to the Seattle area, we will definitely contact Lynn again.

review.name: Like no other tour I've ever been on. So much information, so much fun. Highly recommended.
review.reviewBody:
I am so glad we booked this tour, I learned so much about Seattle and saw many beautiful sights that I was not aware of. Lynn is an excellent guide. She is friendly and very knowledgeable. 
It's obvious that she loves her job. Wish we could have spent the whole day exploring this beautiful city.

review.name: Best tour of our week!
review.reviewBody: Don’t hesitate!  Do this tour.  Our favorite of the week!  We’ve been on several different tours over the last week and Lynn was by far the best tour guide we’ve had. She was well versed in the area and goes at a great pace.  She was attentive to our questions and had so much helpful and interesting information.  She was patient with my mother who has a disability and my daughter who wanted to spend some extra time at the playground at Gas Works Park.  Her car was spotless and she was respectful of our wishes regarding Covid mitigation. Most of all she made the tour fun for US!  She is enthusiastic and makes you feel special.  Thanks Lynn for a great tour!

review.name: Interesting and fun tour!
review.reviewBody: This was a fun tour that included not only the Ballard Locks, Gas Works Park, and Union Lake's houseboats, but a glimpse of native America artifacts at Ivar's and seaplanes landing (and docking) on the lake. Great time with a knowledgeable guide who is willing to tailor the experience to the tour group. Recommended!

review.name: Ballard Locks is very cool
review.reviewBody: On a beautiful day you will enjoy watching how the locks transition boats from sea level to lake level. Pretty cool!
